Name: font

Details:

Categories: Library

Syntax:

Types:

Function: `FProperty font(str fname)`

Synopsis:

Description: Sets the font to be used for text.
See [fontNames] for a list of available fonts.

Examples:
<figure f1.png>
t1 = text("Rascal", font("Serif"), fontSize(20), fontColor("Blue"));
t2 = text("Rascal", font("Monospaced"), fontSize(20), fontColor("Red"));
render(hcat([t1, t2], hgap(10), fontSize(20)));
</figure>
